### Sample CRUD App (MVC) - Port 8000
@mvcHost = http://localhost:8000

### Sample WebFlux App - Port 8002
@fluxHost = http://localhost:8002

### 1. Phase 4: ThreadPool Context Propagation (MVC @Async)
GET {{mvcHost}}/users/async?label=threadpool-test
Accept: application/json

### 2. Phase 3: Reactor Context Propagation (WebFlux)
GET {{fluxHost}}/api/flux/test?label=webflux-test
Accept: application/json

### 3. Phase 3: Reactor Chain & Scheduler Switching
GET {{fluxHost}}/api/flux/chain
Accept: application/json

### 4. Distributed Tracing: MVC -> WebFlux
GET {{mvcHost}}/users/call-flux
Accept: application/json

### -----------------------------------------------------------------------
### Basic CRUD Operations (MVC)
### -----------------------------------------------------------------------

### Create User (Triggers Kafka Produce)
POST {{mvcHost}}/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Jane Doe",
  "email": "jane@example.com"
}

### Get All Users (Triggers DB Query)
GET {{mvcHost}}/users

### Full Chain (HTTP -> DB -> Redis -> Kafka -> HTTP Out)
GET {{mvcHost}}/users/chain

### Bulk Insert (Consecutive DB Queries)
POST {{mvcHost}}/users/bulk?count=5

### -----------------------------------------------------------------------
### Error Scenarios
### -----------------------------------------------------------------------

### Local Error (Simulate 500)
GET {{mvcHost}}/users/error?code=500

### Remote Error (HTTP Out Error)
GET {{mvcHost}}/users/trigger-http-error
